'''Sandor Clegane''', also nicknamed '''The Hound''', is a major character in the [[Season 1|first]], [[Season 2|second]], [[Season 3|third]] and [[Season 4|fourth]] seasons. He is played by starring cast member [[Rory McCann]] and debuts in the [[Winter is Coming (episode)|series premiere]]. Known as the HoundÂ for his savage nature and unquestioning obedience to his masters, Clegane served as the personal bodyguard ofÂ [[Joffrey Baratheon|Joffrey&amp;nbsp;Baratheon]]Â for many years, frequently chafing underÂ Joffrey'sÂ sadistic whims yet always following orders.Â TheÂ Hound is taciturn, brutal, and frequently callous, but not completely without compassion.Â He joined the [[Kingsguard]] when Joffrey took the [[Iron Throne]], but deserted his post during the [[Battle of the Blackwater]].

Following his desertion of the Kingsguard, Clegane leaves [[King's Landing]] only to be captured by the [[Brotherhood Without Banners]]. He wins his freedom after a trial by combat against [[Beric Dondarrion]]. Upon his release, he captures [[Arya Stark]], intending to ransom her to a wealthy relative. His attempts to do so are repeatedly foiled, however, and Arya becomes more of a traveling companion and him her protector. Clegane is critically wounded in a duel with [[BrienneÂ of Tarth|Brienne&amp;nbsp;of Tarth]] when she attempts to assumeÂ guardianship of Arya. His fate is left uncertain when Arya refuses to kill him out of mercy, leaving him for dead on the side of a cliff.

